In a Next.js setup that uses i18n, it's impossible to define redirects via next.config.js that match the source verbatim (ie. not process it by trying to prepend the locale or any such nonsense).

Consider the following next.config.js:

```js
module.exports = {
  i18n: {
    locales: ["de"],
    defaultLocale: "de",
  },

  async redirects() {
    return [
      {
        source: "/google",
        destination: "https://www.google.com",
        permanent: false,
        locale: false,
      },
    ];
  },
};
```

A request to http://localhost:3000/google returns a 404.

I just want to be able to specify redirects verbatim, like in the good ol' days of `.htaccess` …

