In a case like this, the heuristics for webpack's splitChunk in webpack-config.ts seem wrong: 
https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/3dc4b524e79754804b8e53bd1783967d48ce5d13/packages/next/build/webpack-config.ts#L491

At this line, and in the case i'm describing here, `entrypoints` might have a value like the following:

```js
{
  'pages/_app': [ 'private-next-pages/_app.jsx' ],
  'pages/_document': [ 'private-next-pages/_document.js' ],
  'pages/index': [ 'private-next-pages/index.jsx' ],
  'pages/_error': [ 'next/dist/pages/_error' ]
}
```

Which makes the config for the `commons` chunk "wrong" (with `totalPages === 4` instead of arguably `1`):
https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/3dc4b524e79754804b8e53bd1783967d48ce5d13/packages/next/build/webpack-config.ts#L790-L794

As a result, the `commons` chunk tends to be incomplete, and the "slack" is picked up elsewhere (in the `shared` chunks in my current Next.js version, and I'm assuming by multiple individual chunks in the latest canary since `commons` is the lowest priority).

Here's a sample of the Network tabs for such a page

<img width="600" alt="Screenshot 2022-01-17 at 10 08 47" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1325721/149740542-cd9e5d41-4a0b-4fb2-8877-d15c04c291df.png">

Here you can see that there is a single small-ish `commons` chunk, and 2 `shared` chunks (with unnecessary modules in them, but that would not be the case in the latest Next.js canary).


### Expected Behavior

With a single "page", the `commons` chunk should be built based on whether the reason for importing a module can be traced back to that page. Here's a piece of code that looks at imported modules to see if their "import reason tree" can be traced back to the `'pages/_app'` entry point.

```js
function recursiveImportReasonDependencyIsName(module, string) {
	let {reasons} = module
	const visited = new Set()
	visited.add(module._buildHash)
	while (reasons.length > 0) {
		const newReasons = []
		for (let index = 0; index < reasons.length; index++) {
			const reason = reasons[index]
			if (reason.dependency) {
				visited.add(reason.dependency.module._buildHash)
				if (reason.dependency.module.name === string) {
					return true
				}
			}
			if (reason.module) {
				if (visited.has(reason.module._buildHash)) {
					continue
				}
				visited.add(reason.module._buildHash)
				if (reason.module.reasons) {
					newReasons.push(...reason.module.reasons)
				}
			}
		}
		reasons = newReasons
	}
	return false
}

function customSplitChunksCacheGroups(config) {
	if (config?.optimization?.splitChunks?.cacheGroups) {
		delete config.optimization.splitChunks.cacheGroups.commons
		delete config.optimization.splitChunks.cacheGroups.shared

		config.optimization.splitChunks.cacheGroups.commons = {
			name: 'commons',
			chunks: 'initial',
			minChunks: 1,
			priority: 20,
			test: (module) => recursiveImportReasonDependencyIsName(module, 'pages/_app'),
			reuseExistingChunk: true,
		}
	}
}

module.exports = {
	default: customSplitChunksCacheGroups,
}
```

With this config, the `commons` chunk does indeed contain all of the necessary imports. This is the expected behavior:

