### Describe the feature you'd like to request

Idea: Pass diagnostic information to reportWebVitals for CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift), FID (First Input Delay), and LCP (Largest Contentful Paint).[1]

This Codelab from Google, [Measure performance with web-vitals.js, Google Analytics and BigQuery](https://codelabs.developers.google.com/codelabs/web-vitals-google-analytics-bigquery#4), contains some diagnostic helpers to extract more information about CLS, FID, and LCP. The Codelab contains all of the code for these diagnostics, which I'll summarize these below:

For CLS, the diagnostic information might identify the largest layout shift source over the lifecycle of the page view.

For FID, the diagnostic information might identify:
- if FID happened before or after DOMContentLoaded (or the load event)
- Identify the FID target element
- Identify the FID input event type

For LCP, the diagnostic information might identify the element that took the longest.


---

[1]: More info on CoreWebVitals for those curious (https://web.dev/vitals/#core-web-vitals)

### Describe the solution you'd like

Pass diagnostic information to `reportWebVitals`.  This would be done in the [onPerfEntry function](https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/ce6e8b562250f10d4fa9a7dea6e229e363e3baa7/packages/next/client/index.tsx#L294:L326)  in `packages/next/client/index.tsx`.  

For perf reasons, this would opt-in for each piece of diagnostic info. 

Essentially, copying the code in the script tag in the [web-vitals-codelab diagnostics.html](https://github.com/GoogleChromeLabs/web-vitals-codelab/blob/6bafea9d27effc9554e0c426699aa6ecdf4b863e/diagnostics.html#L47:L127).  Excluding the helper functions, the diagnostic function would look something like below.

```javascript
function getDebugInfo(name, entries = []) {
  // In some cases there won't be any entries (e.g. if CLS is 0,
  // or for LCP after a bfcache restore), so we have to check first.
  if (entries.length) {
    if (name === 'LCP') {
      const lastEntry = entries[entries.length - 1];
      return {
