### Describe the feature you'd like to request

## Context

- Since `next@12.1.7-canary.9` Next.js uses one single root middleware instead of nested middleware, which means developers have to declare all middleware logic in one place.
- After https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/37121, Next.js will also execute middleware on internal requests, which might degrade the performance if some heavy logic is being added in the middleware (Adding a `100ms` delay to every `/_next/data` request sounds like a bad idea, especially if developers forget to set a proper `config.matcher`).
- https://github.com/vercel/next.js/pull/37177 allows the middleware to only execute on specific routes, but developers still have to implement their own router in case multiple logic have to be added:

```js
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';

export const config = {
  matcher: [
    '/user/:path*', // Access user control panel requires extra authentication (E.g. SSO based),
    '/register*', // Add extra geo country restriction on register page,
    '/blocked' // We do not allow blocked page to be accessed directly 
  ]
}

export default (req) => {
  if (req.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/user')) {
    // Add extra SSO OAuth based authentication here
  } else if (req.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/register')) {
    if (req.geo.country === 'T1') {
      return NextResponse.rewrites('/blocked');
    }
  } else if (req.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/blocked')) {
    return NextResponse.rewrites('/404');
  }
  return NextResponse.next();
}
```



