```js
  useEffect(() => {
    console.log("index page effect", router.asPath);
  }, [router]);
```

The problem is if we want to navigate to other page when some condition fulfilled, we might write the following code

```js
  const [flag, setFlag] = useState(false);
  const { push } = useRouter();

  useEffect(() => {
    if (flag) {
      push("/other-page");
    }
  }, [flag, push]);
```

And since we implement the page transition, we will render the new page after transition effect is done, but the `push` instance will be updated before we render the new page.

It will cause the effect run multiple times which is not what we expect

I know I can just remove `push` from effect dependencies, I curious about is there any better solution ?

